Who's coming?
Almost no one understands what is happening, even why the whole war has been waged.
"The vacuum created by the lack of facts," said Mr. Englund, "was filled with speculations, assumptions, hopes, fears, prejudices, conspiracy theories, dreams, nightmares and rumors."
"Beautiful and sad" follows the stories of individuals such as Florence Farmborough, an English nurse in the Russian army, and Richard Stumpf, a young sailor serving in the German fleet.
Their stories are all taken from biographies, letters and other already published materials.
The descriptions of their lives may sound horrifying and seductive, but the inclusion of small moments and details makes them absolutely alive and credible.
